LANGOGNE LESPERON,LFHL,FR,4442.179N,00353.050E,1011.0m,2,216,883.0m,50.0m,123.500,"AD reserved for radio-equipped ACFT.\nAsphalt strip 100 x 15 m starting from THR 22, in poor condition.\nRWY 04 and 22 use is limited to :\n - Ultralight ACFT\n - Helicopter\n- Gliders\n- Plane whose pilots can prove :\n* to be home-based ACFT pilots\n* or to be a holder of the mountain license\n* or to have recognized beforehand the platform with an instructor and have used the aerodrome as captain within 12 last months.\n\nProcedures and special instructions\nRWY 04 is preferred RWY for landing.\nRWY 22 is preferred RWY for take-off.\nTouch and go and low height training patterns are prohibited.\nTKOF RWY 04 forbidden for ACFT.\nLDG RWY 22 : presence of trees 89 ft ASFC imposes a plan of approach > 8.5 %. Check performances and LDG distance."
