HINTON IN HEDGES,,GB,5201.683N,00112.567W,149.0m,4,240,695.0m,17.0m,119.455,"Runways 06/24 Hard and Grass.  Tarmac and grass running in parallel.  The south side grass is used primarily for the gliders when the wind direct dictates.  Please talk on the local frequency before entering the right hand circuit\nRunways 09/27.  Grass only.  The grass is used primarily for the gliders when the wind direct dictates.  Please talk on the local frequency before entering the right hand circuit\nRunway 33. Grass only and short.  While landable, 15 should only be used in emergencies.\n\nThere is evidence of a 09/27 concrete - but this is dangerous to land on - 1940's concrete that has now broken up but is usable for driving vehicles and towing gliders.\nThe side of 06/24 hard is also broken.  Stick to the black stuff\n\nThere is a robust group of local power flyers, including an AN-20\n\nThere is a major Sky Dive centre that operates Tuesday to Sunday and Bank holiday Mondays until sunset"
