EAST KIRKBY,,GB,5308.254N,00000.014W,14.0m,2,079,600.0m,20.0m,135.480,"Private aerodrome operated by the Lincolnshire Aviation Heritage Center.\nPilots using East Kirkby do so at thier own risk.\nAll circuits to the South 800ft AAL.\nDo not overfly East Kirkby village nor the house at the NE side of the airfield.\nUse RWY 08/26 in preference. RWY 06/24 inly avbl if specially briefed in advance by telephone.\nDamage area North of the RWY is to be avoided.\nPark on the grass by hedge, not on the apron.\nWARNING: ACFT and aero modellers may operate"
